  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Caucasian race",
    "Age 60-85+ years",
    "At least 2 non-acute clinic visits or annual exams in entire chart",
    "Current use of thyroid medications: require at least 2 fills, with at least one in the year prior to index date",
    "Case Definition 1: ICD9 code for hypothyroidism OR abnormal TSH/FT4 AND thyroid replacement medication use AND at least 2 instances of either medication or lab (combination acceptable) with at least 3 months between first and last instance",
    "Case Definition 2: Positive anti-thyroglobulin antibodies or anti-thyroperoxidase antibodies",
    "Abnormal TSH defined as TSH > 5",
    "Abnormal FT4 defined as FT4 < 0.5",
    "Chart indication of hypothyroidism lasting 3 months or longer: at least 2 mentions at least 3 months apart",
    "Record of abnormal TSH or FT4 lasting 3 months or longer: at least 2 records at least 3 months apart",
    "Control criteria: Normal TSH (0.5-5) and FT4 (0.5-1.2 if checked), no billing codes for hypothyroidism, no thyroid replacement meds",
    "Controls must have at least two Past Medical History sections and Medication lists",
    "Time-dependent exclusion: Pregnancy-related hypothyroidism defined as indication within 6 months before to one year after pregnancy",
    "Time-dependent exclusion: Abnormal labs or medication references within 6 weeks following contrast study",
    "Exclusion: Any use of thyroid-altering medications (Phenytoin, Amiodarone, Lithium, Methimazole, Propylthiouracil)",
    "Control exclusion: Prior history of myasthenia gravis, myasthenia gravis with acute exacerbation, or myasthenia gravis without acute exacerbation",
    "Review period: First year of enrollment at Group Health (enrollment date + 1 year) and last three years prior to index date (index date - 3 years)"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "This phenotype defines chronic autoimmune hypothyroidism (presumptive Hashimoto's hypothyroidism) in Caucasian adults aged 60+ years. Cases must meet one of two criteria: (1) ICD-9 diagnosis codes for hypothyroidism (244, 244.8, 244.9, 245, 245.2, 245.8, 245.9) OR abnormal TSH (>5) or FT4 (<0.5), plus current use of thyroid replacement medications (levothyroxine, synthroid, liothyronine, etc.), with at least 2 instances spanning 3+ months; OR (2) positive anti-thyroglobulin or anti-thyroperoxidase antibodies. Cases are excluded if they have secondary causes (post-surgical/post-ablative hypothyroidism ICD-9 244.0-244.3, thyroidectomy CPT codes), other thyroid diseases (Graves, thyroid cancer, MEN syndromes), pregnancy-related hypothyroidism (within 6 months before to 1 year after pregnancy), contrast-induced hypothyroidism (within 6 weeks of IV contrast), radiation therapy (CPT codes 77xxx), or use of thyroid-altering medications (phenytoin, amiodarone, lithium, methimazole, PTU). Controls must have normal TSH (0.5-5) and FT4 (0.5-1.2), no hypothyroidism diagnoses or thyroid medications, and are additionally excluded for myasthenia gravis. The algorithm reviews the first year of enrollment and the three years prior to index date.",
  "analysis_timestamp": "2026-05-02T20:11:05.407797Z"
}